<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lunadar Darkfyre</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think asked this before, but forgot the answer or waited to long to check.<P>Was/is specialization broken somehow?  I'm pretty sure the only two I bothered putting any points into (alter first then evoke) are both stuck at below average.<P>I haven't been back much since the patch that added the numeric skill but the skills are below 100 so that wouldn't matter.<P>So, can't you have one specialization that's supposed to go higher than 50?<P>I'm almost level 54 something should be up there :b</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You gota put one point into ALL of the spec skills before one goes over 50. My advice is to go train in the skills you havent yet then cast heal over and over  until you see specialize alteration hit 51. then you're good to go.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kregar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Lunadar Darkfyre:<BR><B>I'm pretty sure the only two I bothered putting any points into (alter first then evoke) are both stuck at below average.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>This is your problem. You must put 1 point into each specialization to be able to get 1 of them over 50. I suggest you go put 1 point into the ones that you haven't done yet, then either cast heal over and over OR put a few points into Specialization:Alteration to get it to Average (which is over 51). More than likely Spec:Alteration and Spec:Evocation are sitting at 50 now, so make sure you only cast alteration spells or put that 1 point into Spec:Alteration to bump it to 51 first.<P><P>------------------<BR>Kregar, 50 Priest of Innoruuk<BR>Allied Giants - Ayonae Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, that's a good idea. Go to a guild and try to raise Spec: Alter. You SHOULD get some kind of message telling you that you have reached your max for that skill. THEN put 1 point into each of the other skills you currently have 0 in. (Divination, Convocation and Abjuration) You should get something along the lines of "You learn the basics of XXX". Then you should be able to put one point into specialize alteration and bump to 51. Once you get to 51 on one the others are capped at 50.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">greywolffe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Agree with all previous posters.  Put one point in all specializations then find the lowest spell in each category and chain cast it till you get the skill to 50.  Boring as all get out but well worth it.<P><BR><P>------------------<BR>Greywolffe Silverstarr<BR>51st Cleric of Tunare<BR>E'Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lunadar Darkfyre</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">*sigh*<BR>Almost two years playing this game with a year of that going toward this cleric and I'm still a goof.<P>Thanks for the help.  I guess I'll find my way back to old priests for some more practice.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
